---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import Math from '../components/Math.astro'
import { sourceFile } from '../data/site'
---

<BaseLayout title="Applications">
  <section class="page-intro">
    <div class="site-shell">
      <p class="eyebrow">Applications</p>

      <h1>Natural divergences, Case-type recursion, and Pfaffian applications.</h1>

      <p>
        The first development line culminates in formal proof pipelines for
        renormalized curvature identities under explicit semantic and analytic
        interfaces.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="site-shell grid-2">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Natural Divergences</h3>

        <Math display tex="I=\operatorname{div}F" />

        <Math display tex="\operatorname{RInt}(\operatorname{div}F)=0" />

        <p>
          Under the stated even-dimensional and weight conditions, the
          renormalization package records the vanishing of renormalized
          integrals of natural divergences.
        </p>

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Ambient/PE/Invariants/NaturalDivergence.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open NaturalDivergence.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Case-Type Recursion</h3>

        <Math
          display
          tex="\mathcal L_{n,k,j}(I)=\Delta I-\frac{4(k+j)(n-2k-2j-1)}{n}JI"
        />

        <p>
          The formal recursion tracks exact conformal-weight descent and
          relates base invariants to iterated ambient Laplacians.
        </p>

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Ambient/PE/Invariants/LaplacianRecursion.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open LaplacianRecursion.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Pfaffian-Type Invariants</h3>

        <Math
          display
          tex="P_{\ell,n}=i^*\left(\widetilde\Delta^{n/2-\ell}\operatorname{Pf}_{\ell}(\widetilde{\operatorname{Rm}})\right)"
        />

        <p>
          Pfaffian-like Weyl contractions and ambient counterparts produce
          critical-weight scalar conformal invariants.
        </p>

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Ambient/PE/Invariants/Pfaffian.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open Pfaffian.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Formal Pfaffian Application</h3>

        <Math
          display
          tex="(2\pi)^{n/2}\chi(X)=(-1)^{n/2}(n-1)!!\operatorname{RenVol}(X)+\sum_{\ell=2}^{n/2}c_{n,\ell}\int P_{\ell,n}"
        />

        <p>
          The final application assembles a Gauss–Bonnet-style identity from
          explicit Albin and Pfaffian-reduction certificate inputs.
        </p>

        <a
          class="source-link"
          href={sourceFile('ConformalCovariantOperators/Ambient/PE/Applications/PfaffianApplication.lean')}
          target="_blank"
          rel="noreferrer"
        >
          Open PfaffianApplication.lean ↗
        </a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section border-top">
    <div class="site-shell">
      <div class="note">
        The displayed theorem pipelines are formal results relative to named
        semantic and analytic interfaces. They should not be read as
        unconditional analytic proofs of every external geometric input.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>